Eyyaka Na’abudu Wa Eyyaka Nasta’aeen (1:5)
Ehdina Al-Serata Al-Mustaqeem (1:6)
Serata Al-Lazeena An’amta ‘Alayhim Ghayri Al-Maghdoobi ‘Alayhim Wa Laddaalleen (1:7)

1011
01:16:51,223 --> 01:16:53,702
Dr. Khalifa: Congratulations, you special people.

1012
01:16:54,043 --> 01:16:56,043
A man: (unintelligible) Can I have one?

1013
01:16:56,362 --> 01:16:59,125
Dr. Khalifa: Yes, of course. Was I supposed to?

1014
01:16:59,125 --> 01:17:00,386
A man: (unintelligible)

1015
01:17:00,386 --> 01:17:01,058
Dr. Khalifa: Yeah...

1016
01:17:01,627 --> 01:17:05,511
Delicious drinks. (وَكَأْسًۭا دِهَاقًۭا) [78:34]

1017
01:17:05,511 --> 01:17:13,483
They will never hear in it any nonsense or lies. (لَّا يَسْمَعُونَ فِيهَا لَغْوًۭا وَلَا كِذَّٰبًۭا) [78:35]

1018
01:17:13,483 --> 01:17:22,479
A reward from your Lord; a generous recompense. (جَزَآءًۭ مِّن رَّبِّكَ عَطَآءً حِسَابًۭا) [78:36]

1019
01:17:22,934 --> 01:17:35,684
Lord of the heavens and the earth, and everything between them. The Most Gracious. No one can abrogate His decisions. (رَّبِّ ٱلسَّمَـٰوَٰتِ وَٱلْأَرْضِ وَمَا بَيْنَهُمَا ٱلرَّحْمَـٰنِ ۖ لَا يَمْلِكُونَ مِنْهُ خِطَابًۭا) [78:37]

1020
01:17:36,992 --> 01:17:57,535
The day will come when the Spirit and the angels will stand in a row. None will speak except those permitted by the Most Gracious, and they will utter only what is right. (يَوْمَ يَقُومُ ٱلرُّوحُ وَٱلْمَلَـٰٓئِكَةُ صَفًّۭا ۖ لَّا يَتَكَلَّمُونَ إِلَّا مَنْ أَذِنَ لَهُ ٱلرَّحْمَـٰنُ وَقَالَ صَوَابًۭا) [78:38]

1021
01:17:57,876 --> 01:18:10,171
Such is the inevitable day. Whoever wills let him take refuge in his Lord. (ذَٰلِكَ ٱلْيَوْمُ ٱلْحَقُّ ۖ فَمَن شَآءَ ٱتَّخَذَ إِلَىٰ رَبِّهِۦ مَـَٔابًا) [78:39]

1022
01:18:10,626 --> 01:18:40,895
We have sufficiently warned you about an imminent retribution. That is the day when everyone will examine what his hands have sent forth, and the disbeliever will say, "Oh, I wish I were dust. (إِنَّآ أَنذَرْنَـٰكُمْ عَذَابًۭا قَرِيبًۭا يَوْمَ يَنظُرُ ٱلْمَرْءُ مَا قَدَّمَتْ يَدَاهُ وَيَقُولُ ٱلْكَافِرُ يَـٰلَيْتَنِى كُنتُ تُرَٰبًۢا) [78:40]
